{"word":"πάσχα","slug":"πάσχα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πάσχα, τό</el></b> [of Semitic origin] <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ indecl.\">indecl.</a> <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> Passover,</b> of the Israelite festival of liberation from Egypt <b><a href='B:470 26:2'>Mt 26:2</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> by metonymy, of the Passover meal <b>Passover <a href='B:470 26:18'>Mt 26:18f</a>; <a href='B:480 14:16'>Mk 14:16</a>; <a href='B:490 22:8'>Lk 22:8</a>, <a href='B:490 22:13'>13</a>; <a href='B:650 11:28'>Hb 11:28</a>.</b> Also, of the sacrificial lamb associated <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> the Passover meal, <b>Passover <a href='B:470 26:17'>Mt 26:17</a>; <a href='B:480 14:12'>Mk 14:12</a>, <a href='B:480 14:14'>14</a>; <a href='B:490 22:7'>Lk 22:7</a>, <a href='B:490 22:11'>11</a>, <a href='B:490 22:15'>15</a>; <a href='B:500 18:28'>J 18:28</a>.</b> In imagery, of Christ <b><a href='B:530 5:7'>1 Cor 5:7</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πᾶς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:πάσχω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}